modules.description: This module implements a sum type for handling values that can be one of two distinct types, commonly used for error handling or branching logic. It provides constructors for wrapping values in left or right variants, predicates to check the variant, and transformations to map, fold, or compare values based on their contained type. Concrete use cases include representing computations that may fail (e.g., returning `left` for errors and `right` for successful results) and transforming or inspecting such results without unwrapping them manually.
